bulkATACseq peaks from human brain tissue

Source: R/data.R
CORCES_2020.bulkATACseq_peaks.Rd

Each row represents an individual peak identified in the bulk ATAC-seq data.

CORCES_2020.bulkATACseq_peaks

Format

An object of class data.table (inherits from data.frame) with 186559 rows and 10 columns.

Source

https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.01.06.896159v1

Details

Data originally from Corces et al. (bioRxiv), as of May 2020. Specifically: STable2_Features_bulkATAC-seq_Peaks

See also

Other CORCES_2020: CORCES_2020.HiChIP_FitHiChIP_loop_calls, CORCES_2020.cicero_coaccessibility, CORCES_2020.get_ATAC_peak_overlap(), CORCES_2020.get_HiChIP_FitHiChIP_overlap(), CORCES_2020.prepare_bulkATAC_peak_overlap(), CORCES_2020.prepare_scATAC_peak_overlap(), CORCES_2020.scATACseq_celltype_peaks, CORCES_2020.scATACseq_peaks

Examples

if (FALSE) {
dat <- readxl::read_excel("~/Desktop/Fine_Mapping/echolocatoR/annotations/Coceres_2020/STable2_Features_bulkATAC-seq_Peaks.xlsx", skip = 18)
CORCES_2020.bulkATACseq_peaks <- data.table::data.table(dat)
usethis::use_data(CORCES_2020.bulkATACseq_peaks)
}
